FBIS4-49288 "drchi087_o_94007" FBIS-CHI-94-087 Daily Report 5 May 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Listed Companies Fuel Pudong's Development in Shanghai Listed Companies Fuel Pudong's Development in Shanghai OW0505075594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0730 GMT 5 May 94 OW0505075594 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Shanghai, May 5 (XINHUA) -- The listed companies in the Pudong New Area of Shanghai, China's largest economic center, are leading the area's economic development. Pudong is a newly-established economic zone that is expected to lead the transformation of Shanghai's industrial and financial sectors. According to the latest statistics, Pudong commended 100 robust industrial enterprises last year, and seven of the first ten have listed their stocks on the Shanghai Stock Exchange. These 100 enterprises generated profits totalling 3.323 billion yuan last year, accounting for 77.8 percent of the total in the area. Included was 1.03 billion yuan made by the seven listed companies, about one third of the profits generated by the 100 enterprises. A local official said that these companies are able to raise funds at home and abroad to boost production, and the market economy has forced them to alter their operational mechanism so as to ensure rapid economic growth. Of the 100 industrial enterprises, 17 are listed companies, 24 foreign-funded ones, and the rest major state enterprises and rural industrial businesses.
